  "prompt": "What are the best spell and trap cards in Yu-Gi-Oh?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" spell and trap cards in Yu-Gi-Oh! can be subjective, as it often depends on the current meta and specific deck strategies. However, historically and commonly recognized powerful spell and trap cards include:\n\n**Spell Cards:**\n1. **Monster Reborn** - Allows you to revive a monster from either player's graveyard.\n2. **Raigeki** - Destroys all monsters your opponent controls.\n3. **Harpie's Feather Duster** - Destroys all spell and trap cards your opponent controls.\n4. **Dark Hole** - Destroys all monsters on the field.\n5. **Mystical Space Typhoon** - Destroys one spell/trap card on the field.\n6. **Pot of Greed** - Draws two cards (banned in official play due to its potency).\n\n**Trap Cards:**\n1. **Mirror Force** - Destroys all of your opponent's attack position monsters when they declare an attack.\n2. **Solemn Judgment** - Can negate any spell, trap, or summon, at the cost of half your Life Points.\n3. **Bottomless Trap Hole** - Banishes a monster with 1500 or more ATK when it is summoned.\n4. **Compulsory Evacuation Device** - Returns one monster on the field to the hand.\n5. **Torrential Tribute** - Destroys all monsters on the field when a monster is summoned.\n6. **Infinite Impermanence** - Negates the effect of one face-up monster your opponent controls and can be activated from your hand if you control no cards.\n\nThese cards are staples in many decks and are often seen in competitive play due to their versatility and powerful effects. Keep in mind that card legality can change, and new cards are continually introduced, potentially influencing their popularity and effectiveness.",
